  </header>
  <com>%LC_APP_NAME%</com>
  <comsummary>%TC_APP_NAME% command</comsummary>
  <description>
    <p>The <c>%LC_APP_NAME%</c> escript is a tool whose sole purpose is to
    write binary string greetings to IO.</p>
  </description>
  <funcs>
    <func>
      <name>%LC_APP_NAME% [Options]</name>
      <fsummary>Write binary string greetings to IO.</fsummary>
      <desc>
	<p>%TC_APP_NAME% takes an integer and returns a greeting from
	%LC_APP_NAME% returning the square of the integer supplied.</p>
      </desc>
    </func>
  </funcs>
  <section>
    <title>Exit Status</title>
    <taglist>
      <tag><c>0</c></tag>
      <item>
        <p>Processed successfully.</p>
      </item>
      <tag><c>1</c></tag>
      <item>
        <p>An error occurred</p>
      </item>
    </taglist>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>Options</title>
    <p>The following flags are supported:</p>
      <taglist>
        <tag><c>--version</c></tag>
        <item>
          <p>Print the %LC_APP_NAME% version and exit.</p>
        </item>
        <tag><c>--square &lt;Integer&gt;</c></tag>
        <item>
          <p>Calculate the square of <c>Integer</c> and return that information
	  as a greeting from %LC_APP_NAME%.</p>
        </item>
      </taglist>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <pre>
      <input>$ %LC_APP_NAME% --square 4</input>
      Hello from %LC_APP_NAME%! The square of 4 is 16
    </pre>
  </section>
